<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-05-17T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-05-17T13:00:00-05:00" n="716" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d716">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">838.516/363: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Chapin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-17T13:00:00-05:00">May 17, 1935—1
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 3:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>34. Chamber of Deputies this morning unanimously passed without serious
                            discussion and without modification bill authorizing Government to sign
                            revised contract for purchase of Banque Nationale. Text of bill and
                            contract is the final one forwarded by de la Rue and received here
                            Sunday, a copy of which it is understood was communicated to the
                            Department.</p>
                        <p>Am informed that bill will come up in Senate probably Tuesday where no
                            opposition is of course expected.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Chapin</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>